## 🔧 Backend: ASP.NET Core Projects

### Layer Overview (Clean Architecture / DDD)

```
Core.Shared          ← Shared constants, enums (used by all)
Core                 ← Domain: Entities, Domain Services, Identity
Application.Shared   ← DTOs & Interfaces (shared between backend & client)
Application.Client   ← NETStandard 2.0 client for API consumption (used by MAUI)
Application          ← App Services: business logic
EntityFrameworkCore  ← EF Core DbContext, Repositories, Migrations
Web.Core             ← Shared web code (Auth config, filters, base controllers)
Web.Host             ← Main API (runs on port 44301)
Web.Public           ← Public-facing MVC website (landing page)
Migrator             ← Standalone CLI tool to run DB migrations
GraphQL              ← GraphQL schema and resolvers
Maui                 ← Mobile Blazor Hybrid app
```

---

## 🌐 Web Backend Features (Web.Host)

### Authentication & Identity
- **JWT Bearer** authentication (enabled by default)
- **OpenIddict** OAuth 2.0 / OIDC server (optional, toggle via config)
- **Passwordless Login** with rate limiting
- **Social Login**: Facebook, Google, Twitter, Microsoft, WsFederation, OpenId (all configurable per-tenant)
- **Two-Factor Authentication** (built-in via ASP.NET Identity)
- **LDAP / Active Directory** login (`Abp.Zero.Ldap`)
- **Azure AD / MSAL** integration (via `@azure/msal-browser` on frontend)

### Multi-Tenancy
- Full **subdomain-based** multi-tenancy (`tenant1.yourdomain.com`)
- Per-tenant: settings, features, editions, social login config
- Tenant isolation at the data level (via ABP's `IMustHaveTenant` / `IMayHaveTenant`)
- `DomainTenantCheckMiddleware` prevents non-existent subdomains

### Subscription & Editions (SaaS)
- **Edition management**: define tiers (Free, Pro, Enterprise, etc.)
- **Feature flags per edition**: gate features by subscription level
- **Subscription management**: trial periods, upgrades, renewals
- Payment integration for subscriptions (tied to Stripe/PayPal)

### Payments
- **Stripe**: card payments, webhook support
- **PayPal**: sandbox + production environments
- Both configurable per-tenant and connected to edition subscriptions

### Real-time
- **SignalR** hubs:
  - `/signalr` — General notifications, audit events
  - `/signalr-chat` — Real-time user chat

### Background Jobs
- **Hangfire** with SQL Server storage
- Dashboard protected by permissions (`Pages.Administration.HangfireDashboard`)

### APIs
- **REST API** auto-generated from Application Services
- **Swagger / OpenAPI** UI at `/swagger`
- **GraphQL** endpoint + Playground at `/ui/playground`
- **NSwag** to auto-generate typed Angular API clients

### Security & Infrastructure
- **reCAPTCHA v3** (login, register)
- **CORS** configurable per-origins list
- **Health Checks** UI at `/healthchecks-ui`
- **HTTPS / Kestrel** with certificate config
- **HTML Sanitizer** on all controller inputs
- **Log4Net** logging (separate configs for dev and prod)
- **Azure Key Vault** for secrets (optional)

### Notifications
- User **notification system** (in-app)
- **Mass notifications** to all users or tenants
- **Email** via SMTP / MailKit
- **SMS** via Twilio

### Auditing & Entity History
- Full **audit log** of every API call (user, params, duration, result)
- **Entity change history** — track who changed what on any entity
- GDPR: user data export / deletion requests

### Organization Units
- Hierarchical org tree
- Assign users and roles to org units

### Dynamic Entity Properties
- Add custom properties to any entity at runtime without code changes

### Dashboard Customization
- Users can drag-and-drop dashboard widgets
- Widget definitions stored per-user

