## 💡 What to Keep vs. What to Cut

### ✅ Always Keep (Core)
- `Core`, `Application`, `EntityFrameworkCore`, `Web.Host`
- Users, Roles, Permissions system
- Multi-tenancy (even if single-tenant now)
- Audit Logs (essential for production)

### 🟡 Keep if Building SaaS
- Editions, Features, Subscription management
- Payment integrations (Stripe / PayPal)
- Mass Notifications

### 🔵 Optional / Feature-specific
- Chat (SignalR) — keep if you need real-time messaging
- GraphQL — keep if you have GraphQL consumers
- LDAP — keep if enterprise/corporate users
- Dynamic Entity Properties — rare, keep if you need runtime extensibility
- Dashboard Customization — great UX feature, moderate complexity

### 🔴 Can Be Removed if Not Needed
- `Web.Public` — remove if you don't need a separate public site
- MAUI — remove if web-only
- OpenIddict — only needed if you're building a third-party OAuth server
- Hangfire — can replace with simpler job scheduler if needed
- Social logins — remove any providers you won't use
